    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nIt seems that gh-7676 broke `functools.wraps`:\n```\nimport_tests/test_import.py:14: in <module>\n    @cupy.memoize()\n     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\ncupy/_util.pyx:54: in cupy._util.memoize.decorator\n    ???\n../../../miniforge3/envs/cupy-dev/lib/python3.14/functools.py:56: in update_wrapper\n    setattr(wrapper, attr, value)\nE   TypeError: __annotate__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'format'\n```\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\nimport functools\n\ndef create(f):\n    @functools.wraps(f)\n    def cyfunc():\n        pass\n\n```\nThen call `create()` with somethign like:\n```\ndef myfunc(a : Any):  # has annotations\n    pass\n```\n\nDoing it in pure Cython is a bit hard because Cython attaches an `__annotate__` that *doesn't* need a `format` argument, which is probably why this slipped through.\n\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.2.6\n\n### Additional context\n\n(Broke CuPy CI, but seems likely to cause more issues to me.)",
